NAME

    POE::Devel::Top - Display information about POE sessions and events


DESCRIPTION

    This module displays information about the sessions and events handled
    by the current POE kernel, mimicking the well-known top(1) system
    utility.

    In this early version, it only prints the information on "STDOUT".


INSTALLATION

    To install this module, run the following commands:

        perl Makefile.PL
        make
        make test
        make install

    Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the
    following commands:

        perl Build.PL
        ./Build
        ./Build test
        ./Build install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

    After installing, you can find documentation for this module with
    the perldoc command.

        perldoc POE::Devel::Top

    You can also look for information at:

        RT, CPAN's request tracker
            http://rt.cpan.org/Public/Dist/Display.html?Dist=POE-Devel-Top

        AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
            http://annocpan.org/dist/POE-Devel-Top

        CPAN Ratings
            http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/POE-Devel-Top

        Search CPAN
            http://search.cpan.org/dist/POE-Devel-Top


